When the input string contains not only numbers but also letters, the program throws a NumberFormatException at the line sum += Integer.parseInt(word);. This is because Integer.parseInt() method cannot parse a non-numeric string into an integer.

Example input and output:
Input:
1 2 3 a b c

Output:

Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NumberFormatException: For input string: "a"
	at java.base/java.lang.NumberFormatException.forInputString(NumberFormatException.java:68)
	at java.base/java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Integer.java:662)
	at java.base/java.lang.Integer.parseInt(Integer.java:770)
	at ParseNumbers.main(ParseNumbers.java:16)


